istory as an incomparable illustrator, one whose influence on natural history and book printing still endures today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMammalsvEarly works to 1800. 0aMammalsvPictorial works. 0aMammalsxEarly works to 1800. 0aMammalsxPictorial works. 7aNATURE / General.2bisacsh1 aMartel, Yann.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226044859423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226044859.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles